The paper discusses the design and evaluation of baseband receivers for wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT), Architecture (cs.AR), and Embedded Systems (cs.ET) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the trade-offs between implementation efficiency and communication performance, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents new exploration methodologies for benchmarking implementation efficiency, which is related to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
